James Gordon Jr, fights Harley Quinn and tricks her into a Suicide Collar.

The Thinker gets a hold of the OMAC and attacks Kamo, giving Waller the opportunity she needs to escape.

Deadshot is still alive, and declares he is going to kill Quinn for dropping a mountain on him.

Throughout this whole issue, Waller retells the story of how she found Kamo, raised Killer Shark and the first time she witnessed the true power of OMAC.

Earlier Today: Paris, France- Dyane sees a man on the metro having a hard time standing, then when the man grabs his chest, Dyane tries to help but before she can the man exits the metro followed by two men.

That Night- Dyane finds the man from the Metro floating face down in the river and pulls him to shore. He has a gun shot wound and she offers to help him.

The Next Morning- The man awakes in Dyane's apartment, and after being yelled at by Uncle George, he talks to Dyane. She learns that he has lost his memory and the pair walk around Paris trying to jog his memory. But every time he starts to remember he gets a vision of the Hulk.

Later that day Uncle George is visited by two men, and after he tells them where to find Dyane and the man, they kill him. The two men then locate the man and call him Doctor Banner. Banner escapes then two men, but they then change into large green monsters.

After killing a dozen people, the green monsters catch up to Banner and explode. This is all part of Harrow's plan.
